deck: This winged woman wearing a suit of green armor was a member of the Champions of Angor. She is a possible doppelganger to the Wasp from Marvel Comics.
description:
Creation

T.A. is a fictional character created by Mike McKone and published by DC Comics in June of 1990 is a winged clad young woman in green armor. She appears only in a few panels in Justice League Justice League Quarterly #3 - When You Wish... The woman who has only been named as T.A. on panel, the true meaning for the abbreviated name has never been revealed. She is possibly a pastiche of the Wasp from Marvel Comics.

History

Once Angor was home to many heroes. They also had their fair share of villains although they were never strong enough to cause any major harm. That would change when the extremists obtained nuclear armaments of the world and used them to obliterate all civilization on Angor.

However a handful of survivors made it to Earth to survive their worlds end. One such person was the once owner of the worlds biggest amusement park Mitch Wacky. Mitch decides to return to his dimensional home of Angor and alter its sad ending.

Mitch who during this whole time has been miniaturized as soon as he appears with Kilowog on Angor. Making it to one of Mitch's robotic labs they enter a replica of Mitch. Now controlling a sophisticated robot form the inside both travel to the home-base of the Justifiers (also known as the Champions of Angor) and encounters them in their den. This is were T.A. appears having a conversation with members Bow man and Wandjina. Mitch attempts to warn them however they do not understand Mitch's behavior as anything else but him being well, wacky. T.A. along with the members of the Justifiers attack the Mitch robot assuming it's a trick from an arch villain. Unfortunately they destroy the robot and Mitch is unable to warn them of the Extremists inevitable attack.

T.A. was only seen in a few panels and never appeared again. since the timeline has been changed during several D.C Comic's events her current or possible future appearances are unknown.

Attributes

Hair: Unknown

Eyes: Green

Height: Unknown

Weight: Unknown

Place of origin: Angor

Appearance

T.A. is an attractive young woman with green eyes. She wears a skin tight plunging neck line green metallic bathing suit. She wears long sleeve and thigh high boots of matching green metallic tone. Her hair color has not appeared as she also wears a tight fitting green metallic skullcap. And last but not least T.A. has a pair of light green large wings mounted on her back.

Powers and Abilities

T.A. has only appeared capable of flying. It's assumed that the metallic wings she wears also are the the reason she id also to fly.
name: T.A

deck: Member of the Disciples of Death.
description:
Origin

Barrio Negro is a luchador wrestler who takes part in the underground fighting scene, specifically the "Temple" at Lucha Underground. He is a member of the Disciples of Death, assembled by the mysterious and seductive Catrina and acting as a force for the monster Mil Muertes. When Catrina and Mil Muertes were acting together, they were a massive threat, but with Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece under their command as the Disciples of Death, they would become the dominant force in Lucha Underground.

Creation

Barrio Negro is a fictional character, created by the El Rey Network, for the Lucha Underground show. In 2016, El Rey Network would release a series of comics that use the characters from Lucha Underground, filling in details and plot points between Season One and Season Two.

In the second issue written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr, Catrina and Mil Muertes, as well as the Disciples of Death would be covered.
name: Barrio Negro

deck: Member of the Disciples of Death.
description:
Origin

El Siniestro de la Muerte is a member of the Disciples of Death, mysterious luchador wrestlers who seem obsessed with death. Assembled by Catrina to act as enforcers and henchman for Mil Muerte, they prowl and participate in Lucha Underground fighting scene. Originally Catrina and Mil Muerte operated by themselves. However after Catrina seemed to doubt Mil Muerte's abilities, after losses to Fenix, and Catrina assisting Fenix, the two would separate. It would be a ruse however, with Catrina looking to increase the power of Mil Muerte and after a brief disappearance by both, they would return stronger than ever, this time with three new wrestling talents, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece.

The trio of death obsessed lucha, would target and attack at Catrina's command, and the Trios Champions Son of Havoc, Ivelisse, and Angelico would count among their victims. At one point, the Disciples of Death would challenge the dysfunctional bunch and win the titles off them. This would mirror the success Mil Muerto would continue to have.

Creation

El Siniestro de la Muerte is created by El Rey Network, for use in Lucha Underground. El Siniestro de la Muerte would also appear in the Lucha Underground comics, first appearing in Lucha Underground - Peace Keeper, appearing as the focal point in the following issue, The Throne.
name: El Siniestro de la Muerte

deck: Member of the Disciples of Death.
description:
Origin

Trece along with Barrio Negro, and El Siniestro de la Muerte are the Disciples of Death, mysterious luchador wrestlers who seem obsessed with death. Assembled by Catrina to act as enforcers and henchman for Mil Muerte, they prowl and participate in Lucha Underground fighting scene. Originally Catrina and Mil Muerte operated by themselves. However after Catrina seemed to doubt Mil Muerte's abilities, after losses to Fenix, and Catrina assisting Fenix, the two would separate. It would be a ruse however, with Catrina looking to increase the power of Mil Muerte and after a brief disappearance by both, they would return stronger than ever, this time with three new wrestling talents, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece.

The trio of death obsessed lucha, would target and attack at Catrina's command, and the Trios Champions Son of Havoc, Ivelisse, and Angelico would count among their victims. At one point, the Disciples of Death would challenge the dysfunctional bunch and win the titles off them. This would mirror the success Mil Muerto would continue to have.

Another bizarre objective set by Catrina for the Disciples of Death, would be to gather enough sacrifices, specifically real and raw skulls. These skulls would serve as a base for a macabre and gristly throne for Mil Muerte. Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece would go on a killing spree, slaughtering innocents, to take their heads and skulls, eventually creating Mil Muerte's morbid skull throne. Mil Muerte would use the throne to observe Lucah Underground matches, when he and Catrina would supplant Dario Cueto.

Creation

Trece is a fictional character, created by the El Rey Network, for the Lucha Underground show. In 2016, El Rey Network would release a series of comics that use the characters from Lucha Underground, filling in details and plot points between Season One and Season Two.

In the second issue written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr, Catrina and Mil Muertes, as well as the Disciples of Death would be covered.
name: Trece

deck: Monstrous Luchador Wrestler, The Man of a Thousand Deaths.
description:
Origin

Mil Muertes, The Man of a Thousand Deaths. is a fighter and luchador in the Lucha Underground. The wrestler is a fearsome and intimidating force, however his origins are of a tragic nature. As a young boy in Mexico city, a massive Earthquake would bury Mil Muertes under rubble. He would survive, and manage to crawl out of the destruction and rubble. Unfortunately the rest of his family was not as lucky, they were all dead and he was surrounded by corpses and the cries of others in the background, other victims of the Earthquake.

As an adult, he would participate in Lucha Underground, Dario Cueto's Temple. He would be accompanied by a mysterious and sultry woman, Catrina. Catrina would act as Mil Muertes mouthpiece, the two seeming to have a common interest and fascination with death. Later it would be revealed that Catrina herself is no ordinary mortal being, rather she is extremely long lived, and most likely assisted and guided Mil Muertes, when he was young and trapped in the Earthquake that killed his family.

Acting as his wrestling manager, after Mil Muertes would defeat his opponents, Catrina would slither into the ring, to perform the Lick of Death. She would often intimidate and scheme behind the scenes of the Lucha Underground scene. Eventually Mil Muertes would come across his arch nemesis, Fenix. Where as Mil Muertes was known as The Man of a Thousand Deaths, Fenix, like the mythical creature that is his namesake, is known as The Man of a Thousand Lives. The two would be evenly matched, for a while, eventually though, after a series of losses, Catrina would question Mil Muertes competence and skill, leading to a dissolved alliance. Catrina would then seem to manage and assist Fenix. This too, however was just a manipulation, within a larger manipulation, in order to increase the power of Mil Muertes. The two would reappear after some time, with henchman, the Disciples of Death, and dominate much of the Lucha Underground Temple.

Creation

Mil Muertes is a fictional character, created by the El Rey Network, for the Lucha Underground show. In 2016, El Rey Network would release a series of comics that use the characters from Lucha Underground, filling in details and plot points between Season One and Season Two.

In the second issue written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr, Mil Muertes and Catrina, as well as the Disciples of Death would be covered, in the issue "The Throne".

Character Evolution

Mil Muertes was mostly a monster heel in the first season of Lucha Underground, or since its lucha libre, a rudos. Mil Muertes would also receive somewhat of a power up, after a cunning maneuver by Catrina to increase his abilities.

Major Story Arcs

Season Two

After Dario Cueto's disappearance, Catrina and Mil Muertes assert control and authority over the Temple. With Mil Muerte as the Lucha Underground Champion and the Disciples of Death, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece as Trios Champions, the faction seems to ride a wave of victory. Eventually this string of success would end, as Mil Muerte would rebel against Catrina, the Disciples of Death would lose their Trio championships and then Mil Muerte would lose the Lucha Underground Championship.

Powers and Abilities

Mil Muertes is a very powerful, strong and durable wrestler and fighter in the Lucha Underground Temple. More of a brawler and powerhouse then technical wrestler, he has generally overpowered the other fighters he has encountered. Perhaps only Matanza Cueto has similar strength and power.

Mil Muertes finisher, is the Flatliner.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 6'1"
  • Weight: 245 lbs
  • Eyes: Brown
  • Hair: Brown
name: Mil Muertes

deck: Catrina is a mysterious woman, who has appeared at Lucha Underground and has assisted Mil Muertes, however she is quite deceptive and seems to have ulterior motives.
description:
Origin

Catrina is a seductive, mysterious and shady individual, who first appeared at the Lucha Underground "Temple" and would appear to be an associate and manager for Mil Muertes. Mil Muertes himself, a monstrous luchador wrestler, deeply scarred and troubled from childhood trauma, where he experienced an Earthquake that killed his entire family and left him trapped for days. Catrina would act as Mil Muertes mouthpiece, the two seeming to have a common interest and fascination with death. Later it would be revealed that Catrina herself is no ordinary mortal being, rather she is extremely long lived, and most likely assisted and guided Mil Muertes, when he was young and trapped in the Earthquake that killed his family.

Acting as his wrestling manager, after Mil Muertes would defeat his opponents, Catrina would slither into the ring, to perform the Lick of Death. She would often intimidate and scheme behind the scenes of the Lucha Underground scene. Eventually Mil Muertes would come across his arch nemesis, Fenix. Where as Mil Muertes was known as The Man of a Thousand Deaths, Fenix, like the mythical creature that is his namesake, is known as The Man of a Thousand Lives. The two would be evenly matched, for a while, eventually though, after a series of losses, Catrina would question Mil Muertes competence and skill, leading to a dissolved alliance. Catrina would then seem to manage and assist Fenix. This too, however was just a manipulation, within a larger manipulation, in order to increase the power of Mil Muertes. The two would reappear after some time, with henchman, the Disciples of Death, and dominate much of the Lucha Underground Temple.

Creation

Catrina is a fictional character, created by the El Rey Network, for the Lucha Underground show. She is portrayed by actress and wrestler Karlee Perez (also known as Maxine) on the show. In 2016, El Rey Network would release a series of comics that use the characters from Lucha Underground, filling in details and plot points between Season One and Season Two.

In the second issue written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr, Catrina and Mil Muertes, as well as the Disciples of Death would be covered.

Character Evolution

Catrina would initially appear more innocuous than she would seem. Accompanying the fearsome Mil Muerte, the duo would be very intimidating. It will slowly be revealed that Catrina was much more than would meet the eye. Whilst it was obvious to all at the Temple that Mil Muertes was a threat, his powerful frame and size, fearsome, its most probable that Catrina is even more dangerous. The name Catrina of course, a reference to La Calavera Catrina, La Muerte, death itself.

Major Story Arcs

Trios Championship

One of Catrina's goals, would be to capture the Trios Championships, which would be the titles for the Lucha underground wrestlers who compete in stables of three. She would introduce Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece as the Disciples of Death, a trio that would even defeat the then champions, Son of Havoc, Ivelisse, and Angelico.

Season Two

After Dario Cueto's disappearance, Catrina and Mil Muertes assert control and authority over the Temple. With Mil Muerte as the Lucha underground Champion and the Disciples of Death, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece as Trios Champions, the faction seems to ride a wave of victory. Eventually this string of success would end, as Mil Muerte would rebel against Catrina, the Disciples of Death would lose their Trio championships and then Mil Muerte would lose the Lucha Underground Championship.

Powers and Abilities

Catrina has vague paranormal abilities and powers. Almost supernatural like, but still very mysterious, the extent of them are also unknown. She has shown the ability to teleport, move extremely quickly, seem to endure being choked without showing discomfort or distress, among other unusual abilities. She has claimed to be more than mortal, and almost two centuries old. It may be possible that she is some sort of supernatural being.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 5'4"
  • Weight: 120 lbs
  • Eyes: Brown
  • Hair: Brown
name: Catrina

deck: Luchador who once hunted animals and beasts, but now hunts man.
description:
Origin

King Cuerno is a skilled, methodical luchador wrestler who frequently partakes in the underground Lucha Underground fight scene. King Cuerno is known for his love of the hunt. He formerly hunted various wildlife animals, but after some time and much success, turned his hunter keen eyes towards his fellow humans. Like any good hunter, King Cuerno likes to stalk, observe and calculate ways to defeat his fellow luchadors. Of particular interest to Cuerno, the luchadors Fenix, Prince Puma, and Killshot. King Cuerno doesn't care for the feuds between the good guys or the bad guys, his only interest is the hunt.

At some point, Catrina would cut a deal with King Cuerno, helping him to win the Gift of The Gods title from Fenix. However although the Gift of The Gods title allowed its holder to challenge for the Lucha Underground Championship, and Mil Muertes at the time held the championship, the arrangement was that King Cuerno would hold onto the belt, leaving Mil Muertes unchallenged, save for Catrina selecting his opponents.

Eventually this arrangement broke down with tension between the two, leading to King Cuerno attempting to use his belt to challenge Mil Muertes for his belt, however Catrina would be one step ahead forcing Cuerno to defend the Gift of the Gods from Fenix, which he would be unsuccessful in defending against.
name: King Cuerno

description:
Origin

Son of Havoc is a biker and luchador who participates in the underground fighting scene of the Lucha Underground and the Temple. He also was partnered with another luchador, the very tough and stubborn Ivelisse.
name: Son of Havoc

deck: South African Luchador who often performs death defying moves.
description:
Origin

Angelico is a South African wrestler who participates in the Lucha Underground wrestling scene. Taking place at Dario Cueto's Temple, Angelico took an early interest in the female luchador Ivelisse. Unfortunately Ivelisse isn't really the type of woman to mess around with, and she was also already partnered with the biker and wrestler Son of Havoc. This lead to Angelico not only having matches with Son of Havoc, but against Ivelisse as well. There was a lot of tension and rivalry between the three lucha, and as opportunistic and exploitive as always Dario Cueto would notice this tension and force the wrestlers to team together. Bizarrely despite their infighting and tension, Angelico, Son of Havoc and Ivelisse would go on to have success in the Trios Tournament. Not only would they win their first match, they would win the tournament, becoming the Lucha Underground, Trios Champions.

Unfortunately they would soon find themselves in opposition of Catrina, a mysterious and almost supernatural femme fatale. She had brought together a new group, consisting of Siniestro de La Muerte, Trece and Barrio Negro, also known as the Disciples of Death. These three dark luchadors would succeed in winning the Trios championships away from Angelico, and his teammates.
name: Angelico

deck: The baddest lady in the building. Female luchador and fighter in the Lucha Underground.
description:
Origin

Ivelisse Milagro Vlez is a Puerto Rican wrestler who participates in the Lucha Underground underground fight scene. She is tough and prone to temper and bad moods, which of course can be as much of a benefit as a hindrance in the Temple and Lucha Underground. It also adds some credibility to her claim of being "the baddest bitch in the building". When Ivelisse first started participating in the Lucha Underground, she did so partnered with Son of Havoc, but although she could be very supportive and sweet to Son of Havoc, she often insulted him, especially when he lost, leading to a fractured relationship. This would be a positive for Son of Havoc, as he would go on to defeat Angelico, another fighter who had been attempting to woo Ivelisse. Irony would strike, as Dario Cueto, the head of the Lucha Underground, would force Ivelisse, Son of Havoc and Angelico to team together in a tag team. They would have to also compete in a tournament for the newly created Trios Championship title. Despite the unusual arrangement and preexisting tension and animosity between Ivelisse, Son of Havoc and Angelico, new team would go on to have success, and win the Trios Championship.

Despite initial in fighting outside the ring, their success in the ring would bring the three misfits together well. After considerable time they would lose the Trios Championship to the Disciples of Death members Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece, death obsessed luchadors commanded by Catrina and Mil Muerte.

Creation

Ivelisse is a wrestler for Lucha Underground, created by the El Rey Network. Appearing on the television show, she is also featured in the Lucha Underground comics.

Character Evolution

Like many of the characters from Lucha Underground, and professional wrestling, Ivelisse is an extension and exaggeration of the wrestler themselves, in this case, Ivelisse Milagro Vlez.

Major Story Arcs

Lucha Underground Season Two

Ivelisse would return to the Temple, now on much better terms with her newfound allies, Son of Havoc and Angelico. No longer champions after their defeat at the hands of Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece,, the trio would try and get a championship match with the Disciples of Death. As Dario Cueto had been usurped by Catrina and Mil Muerte, this was a harder task to accomplish, and Catrina being as calculating and manipulate as ever, would instead create a triple threat match between the three, hoping to stir up new tension between the three. The winner would get an opportunity to face Mil Muertes for the Lucha Underground Championship. Despite the circumstance, the triple threat would be respectful, and Ivelisse would pick up the victory after an intense performance. Mil Muerte, would later defeat Ivelisse.

Powers and Abilities

Ivelisse possesses no super human abilities or powers. She is a skilled wrestler/luchador, and know for being a good all rounder. She can grapple, brawl, strike and perform high flying moves.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 5'4"
  • Weight: 115 lbs
  • Hair: Brown
  • Eyes: Brown
name: Ivelisse

deck: Monstrous brother of Dario Cueto.
description:
Origin

Matanze Cueto is a monstrous, dangerous and violent fighter and the brother of Dario Cueto. Dario himself is the owner, boss and head of the Lucha Underground, an underground luchador fighting arena. The brothers have a complicated relationship, as Dario believes Matanza is possessed by some ancient Aztek god like being. In their youths the two boy had no father, only a mother who cared for them. However she was very cruel and abusive, prone to getting drunk and abusing her children. The two young boys, would often play and enjoy each others company, but they would fear the violent beatings received. After one particularly brutal beating at the hands of their mother on Dario, Matanza would snap, and attack his mother with a heavy bronze bull statuette, in defense of Dario. Their abusive mother dead, Dario and Matanza were now free.

In the years after, at some point, Matanza would seem too dangerous to be free. Dario would keep his now massive and powerful brother locked away, although, this arrangement seemed to not instill too much resentment in Matanza.
name: Matanza

deck: The shady boss, owner and promoter of Lucha Underground.
description:
Origin

Dario Cueto is the owner, boss and head of the Lucha Underground, an underground luchador fighting arena. Dario would form the Temple, a wrestling arena that would host the fights. Whilst entertaining and violent fighting, and shrewd business deals leading to profit, seem to be Dario's main motivation in creating the Temple to house Lucha Underground, he also seems to have ulterior motives, of a somewhat more sinister and supernatural nature. After acquiring many luchador talents, Dario would entice the fighters of the Temple into putting on especially entertaining and violent fights, with money, and unique opportunities. His head office not located far from the ring, actually overlooking it, Dario is the sort of boss, that if a wrestling fight spills into his room, he will smile with glee and mix a cocktail so he can observe and appreciate the action up close.

Dario Cueto is not a fair and impartial boss or owner however. He has his own agenda, preferences and objectives. He has had feuds with of the Lucha Underground wrestlers, notable talent such as Mil Muertes, Catrina, Pentagon Jr, Johnny Mundo, Son of Havoc, Ivelisse and Angelico. However for every enemy he has had, he has also had an ally or enforcer to do his bidding. His most intimidating and monstrous enforce, actually being his very own brother, Matanza Cueto.

In their youth, as children, the two brothers were fond of games, and fun. They did not know their father, and their mother was abusive and violent. After one particularly brutal beating at the hands of their mother on Dario, Matanza would snap, and attack his mother with a heavy bronze bull statuette, in defense of Dario. Their abusive mother dead, Dario and Matanza were now free.

Creation

Dario Cueto is a character from Lucha Underground.

Character Evolution

Dario Cueto plays very much into the slick and evil boss archetype, albeit one that is so irredeemably corrupt, self serving, and greedy as to attract a certain amount of fandom despite being a villain.
name: Dario Cueto

deck: A ruthless, violent, crazed luchador, who participates in the Lucha Underground.
description:
Origin

The illegal underground fighting league, the Lucha Underground attracts many dangerous, ruthless, and sadistic fighters, but one of the, if not most, violent, sadistic and dangerous luchador it has attracted is Pentagon Jr. Dario Cueto would envision Pentagon Jr as a valuable asset to have for his Temple. Pentagon Jr had long felt he had not received enough respect and gratitude from Mexican fans. Pentagon, obsessed with injuring and hurting is opponents, would begin to gain a reputation for being overly sadistic and violent. Even more so when he would begin dedicating his unique brand of violence and wrestling to an unseen master. Eventually this would turn out to be Vampiro, despite his alter Ian Richard Hodgkinson being a color commentator for Lucha Underground. After beginning a new technique, Pentagon would go on to break the arms of several Lucha Underground competitors, such as Argenis and Super Fly.

In a daring and bold move, Pentagon Jr would even attack and break the arm of then champion Mil Muerte.

Creation

Pentagon Jr is a fictional character, created by the El Rey Network, for the Lucha Underground show. In 2016, El Rey Network would release a series of comics that use the characters from Lucha Underground, filling in details and plot points between Season One and Season Two.

Pentagon Jr and his story would be covered in the third issue written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr.

Major Story Arcs

Season Two

Stronger and more violent than ever after defeating his former mentor, Pentagon Jr would have several rivalries with different other lucha wrestlers. This would culminate in a feud between Pentagon Jr and Matanza and Dario Cueto.
